  "text": "12e14 Combined supplementation of vitamin C and vitamin E is the best choice for antioxidant treatment. As a result of continuous oxidative stress, there is an increase in the concentration of ascorbate radical that shows as a peak followed by a steady decline. After disappearance of the ascorbate radical, the tocopheroxyl radical appears. [CITATION_1] This study aimed to investigate whether combined supplementation of vitamin C and vitamin E was able to modify the superoxide dismutase (SOD) and malondialdehyde (MDA) levels in the ovarium of rats exposed to rhodamine B. In addition, the effects on endometrial histology were also explored.",
